When dealing with string there may be cases when we might want to:

Check whether a string contains any whitespace
Change the characters to lowercase/upppercase
See whether a given character is present,etc.

FUNCTIONS USED TO PROCESS CHARACTERS
isalnum(c)- True if c is a letter or a digit.Return true if its returns A B C 1 2 3.Alphanumeric.
isalpha(c)- True if c is a letter.(A B C.)
iscntrl(c)- True if c is a control character.(\t \n \b \r.)
isdigit(c)- True if c is a digit.A B C.
isgraph(c)- True if c is not a space but is printable.(A a 1.)
islower(c)- True if c is a lowercase letter.(a b c.)
isupper(c)- True if c is a uppercase letter.(A B C.)
isprint(c)- True if c is a printable character.(A b c 1 2.)
ispunct(c)- True if c is a punctuaction character.(! , . # $ @.)
ispsace(c)- True if c is a whitespace.('' \n-newline \t-tab.)
isxdigit(c)- true if c is a hexadecimal digit.(A B C D E F.)
tolower(c)- Change c to lowercase if it an upppercase letter.Otherwise leaves it unchanged.
(A - a,B - b,C - c)
toupper(c)- Chnge c to uppercase if it is a lowercase letter.Otherwise leaves it unchanged.
(a - A,b - B,c - C)
